# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Philos — .gitignore
#
# What this file does: tells git which files to *never* commit.
# Why we care: copyrighted PDFs, generated artifacts, and secrets must
# stay local. Only the code and project scaffolding go into version control.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Python bytecode & build artifacts ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# --- Virtual environments ---
# We don't prescribe a venv name; ignore all common ones.
.venv/
venv/
env/
.python-version

# --- Secrets ---
# Never commit real API keys. .env.example (committed) shows the shape;
# .env (ignored) holds the real values.
.env
.env.local

# --- Data directories ---
# Raw PDFs may be copyrighted and are always user-supplied.
# Processed chunks/indexes are deterministic outputs — regenerate them.
data/raw/*
data/processed/*
# ...but keep the directories themselves in the repo via .gitkeep files.
!data/raw/.gitkeep
!data/processed/.gitkeep

# --- Future: vector store persistence (added in Round 2) ---
chroma/
*.chroma

# --- Editor / OS cruft ---
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
